    <header class="article-header pt-3 pb-8" id="article-top">
      <h1 title="Stereo Speakers Vs Monitors with Reference" class="text-3xl font-medium leading-tight">
        Stereo Speakers Vs Monitors with Reference
        
        
        

            

            
            
        
      </h1>

      <div class="article-author pt-4">
        <div class="flex items-center">
          <div class="avatar article-avatar">
            
            <img src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/19e98985b59a127561026f9deb0036bd?default=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.zendesk.com%2Fhc%2Fassets%2Fdefault_avatar.png&amp;r=g" alt="Avatar" class="user-avatar h-16 rounded-full" />
          </div>
          <div class="article-meta pl-3 pb-1">
            
              Adam Price
              <a class="post-subscribe" title="Opens a sign-in dialog" rel="nofollow" role="button" data-auth-action="signin" data-follower-count="1" aria-selected="false" href="/hc/en-us/community/posts/360006591439-Stereo-Speakers-Vs-Monitors-with-Reference/subscription.html">Follow</a>
            <div class="article-updated meta-data text-regular text-sm">Updated <time datetime="2019-11-19T07:55:42Z" title="2019-11-19T07:55:42Z" data-datetime="relative">November 19, 2019 07:55</time></div>
             		<div class="post-published meta text-regular text-sm">
                  <time datetime="2019-11-14T10:56:18Z" title="2019-11-14T10:56:18Z" data-datetime="calendar">November 14, 2019 10:56</time>
                </div>
             

              
            </div>
        </div> 
      </div>
    </header>
    
    

    <section class="article-info">
      <div class="article-content">
        <main class="article article-body text-justify">
          <p>I am a current user of Sonarworks Reference 4 and love it on my existing Yamaha MSP7 and HS8 &amp; HS8S</p>
<p>I also have some old, very large 3-way Teac audiophile speakers and am using Sonarworks on them too and the response is nice and flat down to 30hz.</p>
<p>I just want to know, is this ok to mix on these large speakers as opposed to buying large PSI a23m type specific speakers as an upgrade?</p>
<p>As I can certainly here lots of things I cannot hear on the large Teac's that I cannot hear on the smaller 7" and 8" Yamaha's.</p>
<p>My thoughts are that with Sonarworks makeing the large Teac's flat and they are with Sonarworks then it should be ok?</p>
<p>Translation seems good, outside also, but are there any issues you guys see by me doing this?</p>
<p>I'm tossing up whether to get the PSI's or not and why should I over not getting them?</p>
<p>Thoughts anyone?</p>
        </main>

      </div>
    </section>

